1
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,467
A large part
of the mountain collapsed

2
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:48,333
here in Barangay Pinagkaisa.

3
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:51,700
That's our barangay!

4
00:00:51,767 --> 00:00:53,067
Emma! Emma!

5
00:00:53,133 --> 00:00:54,600
You're in an evacuation center.

6
00:00:54,667 --> 00:00:55,767
You were found
unconscious on the street.

7
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:57,167
That's why you
were brought here.

8
00:00:57,233 --> 00:00:58,433
My daughter. Where's my
daughter?

9
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,567
There was no child with you
when you were brought here.

10
00:01:00,633 --> 00:01:02,700
Where's our daughter?

11
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:05,100
Where's Kayla?

12
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:07,567
Why isn't she with you?
Where's Kayla?

13
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:11,133
If you only had listened to me,
and gave Kayla up for adoption,

14
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:12,433
this wouldn't have happened.

15
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:15,400
Can you do it
to your own child?

16
00:01:15,467 --> 00:01:18,067
Can you give your child
away to someone you don't know?

17
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:21,767
If I have to,
and there's a chance, yes!

18
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,600
But I don't understand.

19
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:26,367
Why were you only with us
for a short while?

20
00:01:26,433 --> 00:01:28,333
Hello, little darling.

21
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,667
- Sleep well, my little...
- Olive, I'm here!

22
00:01:35,733 --> 00:01:37,467
- We have a monthly report...
- don't come in here...

23
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:40,000
I'm just going to give this...

24
00:01:42,267 --> 00:01:43,800
Why is there a crib?

25
00:01:43,867 --> 00:01:46,167
And...

26
00:01:46,233 --> 00:01:48,433
is that a baby?
Whose baby is it?

27
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:50,200
This is my baby.

28
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:52,300
She's Maria Angela.

29
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:54,100
Did you adopt a kid?

30
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:56,200
Yes.

31
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:13,067
In Jesus' name,

32
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,933
- Amen.
- Amen.

33
00:02:27,067 --> 00:02:28,400
It's just sad.

34
00:02:30,667 --> 00:02:35,133
We're celebrating Kayla's first
birthday without her.

35
00:02:37,167 --> 00:02:40,133
Why are you giving
yourselves a hard time?

36
00:02:41,433 --> 00:02:44,267
You should've
just lit a candle.

37
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:47,367
Baby Kayla isn't here
to enjoy this.

38
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:51,433
Mom, we promised Baby Kayla

39
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:54,433
that we would still celebrate
her birthday, even without her.

40
00:02:55,767 --> 00:02:56,533
So that...

41
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:01,133
our child's memories remain.

42
00:03:10,133 --> 00:03:11,733
Dear,

43
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:15,933
I've saved up for your birthday
for a long time.

44
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,700
She looks so adorable.

45
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:27,600
Look at that cute little
heart-shaped birthmark.

46
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:30,533
I remember Angela in her.

47
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:36,200
I'd do everything if given
another chance,

48
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:39,100
to get my daughter back.

49
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:47,533
Isn't this the baby in the NICU?

50
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:51,433
I remember she had
the same birthmark.

51
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:54,367
Olive,

52
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:57,333
did you steal that baby?

53
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:40,233
Olive!

54
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:42,200
are you out of your mind?

55
00:04:42,767 --> 00:04:46,267
Why did you do that?
Why did you steal that child?

56
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:48,700
Relax, Astrid.

57
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:52,767
I only took my child.

58
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:56,067
- Olive, bring that child back.
- No.

59
00:04:56,133 --> 00:04:57,667
When I saw this child,

60
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:03,333
I felt Baby Angela in her.

61
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:05,567
Angela? Maria Angela?
Your daughter?

62
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:06,933
Yes!

63
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:15,733
They have the same smile,
laugh, and cry.

64
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:20,600
Even the way she holds
my finger is like Maria Angela.

65
00:05:20,667 --> 00:05:22,133
Olive!

66
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,600
What are you saying?

67
00:05:26,233 --> 00:05:27,667
I believe...

68
00:05:29,567 --> 00:05:32,600
that my child's soul
transferred to this baby.

69
00:05:32,667 --> 00:05:34,533
Trust me.

70
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:37,200
She is my daughter.

71
00:05:37,267 --> 00:05:40,067
Olive, she's not your daughter.

72
00:05:40,133 --> 00:05:41,567
Your child is dead.

73
00:05:44,467 --> 00:05:48,100
I may have lost my daughter
in a car accident, but...

74
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:52,333
because of this child,

75
00:05:54,533 --> 00:05:59,400
I was given a second chance
to be with my daughter again.

76
00:05:59,467 --> 00:06:02,567
Olive, that's just
your depression talking.

77
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:04,633
I'm not depressed!

78
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:06,133
I'm fine!

79
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,633
You can go to jail
if the police learn about this.

80
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:10,500
You will lose everything.

81
00:06:15,433 --> 00:06:16,433
Well...

82
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:24,467
the police must not
know about this.

83
00:06:24,533 --> 00:06:25,633
Unless...

84
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,367
you will report me.

85
00:06:31,533 --> 00:06:32,333
Will you?

86
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,167
Remember,

87
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,467
you're indebted to me.

88
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:49,267
My parents sent you to school.

89
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:58,133
I also brought you into
our family's businesses.

90
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:01,300
It's because of me,

91
00:07:03,167 --> 00:07:06,300
that's why you have everything
you have right now

92
00:07:08,667 --> 00:07:12,300
But if you try to take
this baby away from me,

93
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:17,933
I will take everything back.

94
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:21,333
And I will make your life

95
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,567
a living hell.

96
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:34,000
So, Astrid...

97
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:42,300
Will you report me?

98
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:48,367
Thank you, Astrid.

99
00:07:52,267 --> 00:07:55,467
I hope you understand
where I'm coming from.

100
00:07:57,133 --> 00:07:59,500
And to be honest,

101
00:07:59,567 --> 00:08:01,633
I don't really expect
you to understand

102
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:04,233
because you don't have a child.

103
00:08:06,167 --> 00:08:07,167
But you know what?

104
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,233
This baby...

105
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:17,100
she has brought back
so much joy into my life.

106
00:08:19,067 --> 00:08:22,233
It's like I've forgotten
everything that happened.

107
00:08:24,767 --> 00:08:25,533
So, please.

108
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:32,000
Please don't ever
take her away from me.

109
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:46,200
I'll give this child
a good life...

110
00:08:48,267 --> 00:08:51,433
even more than
her parents can give her.

111
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,533
They should thank me.

112
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:00,367
Because I'm doing them a favor.

113
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:09,967
They can't give Mookie all
her needs the same way I can.

114
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,500
Mookie?

115
00:09:12,567 --> 00:09:13,267
Yes.

116
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:19,267
That's what I will call her.

117
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:20,300
But Olive,

118
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:25,200
are you sure
you're ready to care for a baby?

119
00:09:25,267 --> 00:09:26,900
It's a big responsibility.

120
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:31,300
I may be reckless
with my first baby...

121
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:38,467
but I'll make sure not to repeat
the same mistakes.

122
00:09:43,033 --> 00:09:45,000
This time I'll be better.

123
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:51,333
Because I'm more ready
to become a mother now,

124
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,533
to Mookie.

125
00:09:58,667 --> 00:10:01,167
Just leave the documents
I have to sign.

126
00:10:02,533 --> 00:10:04,200
You can go now.

127
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,400
Mommy's here.

128
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:22,133
I imagine...

129
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,633
preparing delicious food
for you.

130
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,467
And...

131
00:10:28,533 --> 00:10:32,433
I'll invite all
our friends and families.

132
00:10:33,533 --> 00:10:36,300
And I'll fill
the house with balloons.

133
00:10:44,733 --> 00:10:47,433
But why does it seem like
the opposite happened?

134
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,300
Dear...

135
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:56,200
I know right now...

136
00:10:58,167 --> 00:10:59,500
you're watching us.

137
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:04,367
You're now
our guardian angel, right?

138
00:11:06,367 --> 00:11:08,433
Mom's wish for you,

139
00:11:08,533 --> 00:11:09,500
I hope that...

140
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,400
in the afterlife....

141
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:16,567
we'll be together again.

142
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:24,367
Happy birthday,
my dear daughter.

143
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:21,100
Good morning, birthday girl!

144
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:23,033
Hold on.

145
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,967
Let's remove it.

146
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:38,067
I can't believe it, dear.

147
00:12:38,833 --> 00:12:40,567
You're now 17.

148
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:45,600
I can't believe it, dear.

149
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:48,033
You're now 17.

150
00:12:48,133 --> 00:12:49,633
I know, Mom.

151
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:54,333
One more year,
and I'll be an adult.

152
00:12:55,633 --> 00:12:56,500
You know what?

153
00:12:57,667 --> 00:13:02,333
I still remember those days
when the doctor said...

154
00:13:04,233 --> 00:13:07,500
I'd be lucky
if you reached 8 years old.

155
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,300
But here you are.

156
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:13,267
You're still with me.

157
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:17,233
That's why Mommy,

158
00:13:17,300 --> 00:13:19,367
every day is a blessing.

159
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,567
Can you get up?

160
00:13:26,633 --> 00:13:27,700
Slowly.

161
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,000
Are you okay?

162
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:36,400
You look exhausted.

163
00:13:38,233 --> 00:13:41,700
Maybe we should cancel
your party later.

164
00:13:41,767 --> 00:13:43,433
No, Mommy.

165
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,100
I'm fine, I can do it..

166
00:13:46,233 --> 00:13:50,433
I've actually waited for my
birthday party for a long time.

167
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,667
Okay.

168
00:13:54,767 --> 00:13:56,500
But...

169
00:13:56,567 --> 00:13:58,567
drink your meds first.

170
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:00,967
Here.

171
00:14:20,033 --> 00:14:21,533
That's my girl.

172
00:14:34,067 --> 00:14:35,767
We're going to sing now.
There you go.

173
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,200
Okay.

174
00:14:37,267 --> 00:14:43,500
Happy birthday to you!

175
00:14:53,567 --> 00:14:55,667
And, of course,

176
00:14:55,733 --> 00:14:58,400
here's my gift for you, Mookie.

177
00:14:58,467 --> 00:15:01,067
- Wow!
- Happy birthday, sweetheart.

178
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:10,200
You have to be careful.

179
00:15:10,267 --> 00:15:12,433
Remember, it's for display.

180
00:15:14,633 --> 00:15:16,233
Okay, Mommy.

181
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:19,233
Thank you. It's so beautiful.

182
00:15:23,033 --> 00:15:28,967
And, by the way, thank you
so much for coming, Aunt Astrid,

183
00:15:29,033 --> 00:15:31,033
despite your busy schedule.

184
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,233
Of course, anything for you.

185
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:36,967
But, Mookie, what did you
wish for your birthday?

186
00:15:37,067 --> 00:15:39,133
My wish?

187
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:42,700
I wish for my healing.

188
00:15:42,767 --> 00:15:45,200
And...

189
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:48,333
I wish to live the life
of a normal teenager.

190
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,133
You're folding papers again.

191
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:29,000
I'm just killing time.

192
00:16:29,067 --> 00:16:34,400
It feels better to think that
our daughter is now a star.

193
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:38,300
And she's watching us
from heaven.

194
00:16:38,367 --> 00:16:39,567
Mommy!

195
00:16:39,633 --> 00:16:42,133
Can I eat ice cream?

196
00:16:43,567 --> 00:16:45,667
Is this the sugar-free
avocado ice cream?

197
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:47,400
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Are you sure?

198
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:48,700
- Yes.
- Okay.

199
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,700
You can have one,
but don't eat all of it.

200
00:16:52,767 --> 00:16:54,700
It might spoil your appetite.

201
00:16:54,767 --> 00:16:57,067
- Go ahead.
- Thank you.

202
00:17:03,533 --> 00:17:05,467
Are you sure
this isn't pistachio?

203
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:07,633
Yes, Ma'am.

204
00:17:12,033 --> 00:17:14,167
This is pistachio!

205
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:16,367
- Ma'am?
- Are you stupid?

206
00:17:16,467 --> 00:17:20,100
Mookie is allergic to peanuts!

207
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:22,667
Do you know what can happen
to her because of what you did?

208
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:24,400
- Sorry...
- her throat could close,

209
00:17:24,467 --> 00:17:26,033
and she could die!

210
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:28,067
You're so stupid!

211
00:17:28,133 --> 00:17:29,967
Get out of my face!

212
00:17:30,033 --> 00:17:31,633
Get lost!

213
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:33,467
Stupid!

214
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:36,300
- Flor! Get the medicine! Hurry!
- Yes, Ma'am.

215
00:17:36,367 --> 00:17:39,100
Are you okay? Can you breathe?
Are you okay?

216
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:41,467
- Hurry up!
- Yes, Ma'am. Here it is!

217
00:17:41,533 --> 00:17:42,167
Wait, dear.

218
00:17:42,233 --> 00:17:44,100
Here you go. Excuse me, Ma'am.

219
00:17:48,633 --> 00:17:50,533
- Open.
- Water, water.

220
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,633
That was close.

221
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,533
Are you okay?

222
00:18:04,567 --> 00:18:06,133
It's okay. You're gonna be fine.

223
00:18:08,533 --> 00:18:10,467
That was a close call.

224
00:18:10,533 --> 00:18:13,267
If I didn't notice that your
ice cream has pistachio nuts,

225
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:14,900
then you could've died.

226
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:18,233
But don't worry.

227
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:20,600
I fired that maid.

228
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:23,167
I feel bad for Jenny.

229
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:26,467
Well, that's what she gets
for being so stupid.

230
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:29,100
I told her many times about
all the food you can't eat,

231
00:18:29,167 --> 00:18:32,733
and yet she still bought
that ice cream.

232
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:35,133
I cannot let this happen again.

233
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,633
Not with your condition.

234
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:39,567
Go on, dear.

235
00:18:39,633 --> 00:18:41,633
Get some rest.

236
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:44,700
But Mommy, what about
my birthday party?

237
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:46,300
It's over.

238
00:18:46,367 --> 00:18:47,967
I sent your Aunt home.

239
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,467
But Mommy...

240
00:18:50,533 --> 00:18:53,000
Mookie, please.

241
00:18:53,067 --> 00:18:54,033
Don't be stubborn.

242
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:57,400
To begin with,

243
00:18:57,467 --> 00:18:59,600
I really didn't want to continue
with your birthday party.

244
00:18:59,667 --> 00:19:00,933
Because I had a gut feeling

245
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,200
that something bad
would happen to you.

246
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:03,500
And true enough!

247
00:19:03,567 --> 00:19:05,967
This is what happens to you.

248
00:19:06,033 --> 00:19:08,500
I should've listened
to my intuition.

249
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:11,300
So, go ahead.

250
00:19:11,367 --> 00:19:13,000
Get some rest, okay?

251
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:14,067
Get some rest.

252
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:34,167
Poor Mookie.

253
00:19:34,233 --> 00:19:36,533
She only celebrates
her birthday once a year.

254
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:38,267
And it was interrupted.

255
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:42,067
Jenny's dumb.

256
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:45,000
I told her the kid
has many allergies.

257
00:19:45,067 --> 00:19:47,033
Can you blame her?

258
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:49,167
It's also green,
like the avocado.

259
00:19:53,633 --> 00:19:56,733
But wait.

260
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,700
What's that kid's illness?

261
00:19:59,767 --> 00:20:02,567
That puzzled me.

262
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:04,600
Malou, I brought you here

263
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:08,100
to be a housekeeper,
not a gossiper.

264
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:11,500
- Come on.
- Finish what you're doing.

265
00:20:11,567 --> 00:20:13,000
It's too early.

266
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:14,967
I'm busy, so stop
asking questions.

267
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:25,700
Okay.

268
00:20:25,767 --> 00:20:27,333
Okay, Mommy.

269
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,467
Why is the tablet here?

270
00:20:36,567 --> 00:20:37,533
Didn't I tell you

271
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:40,533
that you can only use this
for school purposes?

272
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:44,533
I only use that
when I'm bored, Mommy.

273
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:49,533
And I watch my favorite shows.

274
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:53,033
Didn't I tell you that
you can't stay up late?

275
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:55,433
You should rest.

276
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:57,667
Do you know
what chronic sleep deprivation

277
00:20:57,733 --> 00:20:59,633
can do to your body?

278
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:01,733
You can have
high blood pressure.

279
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:03,733
You can get a stroke.

280
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,267
Diabetes, and so on
and so forth.

281
00:21:09,100 --> 00:21:11,467
What are you watching?

282
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:14,567
Family drama...

283
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:16,267
romantic movies.

284
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,633
Mookie, dear.

285
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:23,000
You shouldn't be watching
things like this.

286
00:21:23,067 --> 00:21:26,533
The next time I catch you
watching shows like this,

287
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,467
I will take your tablet.

288
00:21:28,533 --> 00:21:29,700
I'm telling you this

289
00:21:29,767 --> 00:21:32,467
because I don't want you
to get your hopes up.

290
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:36,433
I don't want you to think

291
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:41,567
that those you watch
will also happen to you.

292
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:48,400
With your condition,
you'll never be normal.

293
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:52,333
And you'll never find
someone who will love you.

294
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:56,167
And let's just say that you do.

295
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:58,133
Trust me.

296
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:01,100
That someone will leave you.

297
00:22:01,167 --> 00:22:04,600
Because he will see
you as a burden.

298
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:07,267
Someone who needs
to be taken care of.

299
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:15,367
It's my payday today.

300
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:18,433
If you like, we can eat out.

301
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:21,367
There's a newly opened
restaurant in town.

302
00:22:21,433 --> 00:22:24,000
It's been a while since
we last went on a date.

303
00:22:25,133 --> 00:22:26,600
Do you want to go?

304
00:22:26,667 --> 00:22:27,633
No.

305
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:31,033
Let's not spend money on that.

306
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:33,267
We still have a lot
of debt to pay.

307
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:36,333
I don't want you moping
in the house.

308
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:37,167
Oh, boy.

309
00:22:38,833 --> 00:22:41,600
That's what I tell your wife.

310
00:22:41,667 --> 00:22:43,567
She should go out sometimes.

311
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:45,767
Go out with me.

312
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,500
But, nothing.

313
00:22:47,567 --> 00:22:50,433
I think she would
rather be a hermit.

314
00:22:50,533 --> 00:22:54,233
Hey, Emma,
you should enjoy life.

315
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,200
Look at me. I look so young.

316
00:22:56,267 --> 00:22:57,367
Right?

317
00:22:57,433 --> 00:22:58,367
Yes, Mom.

318
00:22:58,433 --> 00:23:00,433
Thanks.

319
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:02,667
I'll take a bath now.
I'm so dirty.

320
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:04,533
Dan,

321
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:07,267
don't worry about me.

322
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:08,500
I'm okay.

323
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,233
Okay.

324
00:23:11,300 --> 00:23:14,333
I'll go home early, okay?

325
00:23:16,167 --> 00:23:17,233
Bye.

326
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:33,033
I will always be here for you.

327
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,767
I will always take care of you.

328
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:42,300
I will give you
everything you need.

329
00:23:42,367 --> 00:23:44,067
And I will always love you.

330
00:23:44,133 --> 00:23:46,567
And I will always try my
best to understand you.

331
00:23:48,567 --> 00:23:50,633
So it's just you and me

332
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:52,400
for the rest of our lives.

333
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:55,367
Do you get it, sweetie?

334
00:23:58,333 --> 00:24:00,100
Yes, Mommy.

335
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:03,000
You and me forever.

336
00:24:50,567 --> 00:24:52,267
I have someone
to introduce to you.

337
00:24:52,333 --> 00:24:53,100
This is Samantha.

338
00:24:53,167 --> 00:24:54,467
She's the one
I was telling you about.

339
00:24:54,533 --> 00:24:56,767
Can you handle
the responsibility?

340
00:24:56,833 --> 00:24:59,300
You might get
attached to the kid.

341
00:24:59,367 --> 00:25:01,967
What will happen when Melissa
comes back to get her?

342
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:02,933
You might get hurt.

343
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:06,467
Didn't I tell you
that you can't go out?

344
00:25:06,533 --> 00:25:09,633
Because you disobeyed me,
you'll stay in the dark room.

345
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:11,667
No, Mommy! Please!

346
00:25:11,733 --> 00:25:13,733
Come on. Don't you feel
bad for Mookie?

347
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:15,533
What can I do?

348
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:18,667
What if you report
it to the Bantay Bata?

349
00:25:18,733 --> 00:25:21,433
Mookie's condition
is very complex.

350
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:23,467
But have you taken
her to the hospital?

351
00:25:23,533 --> 00:25:24,467
Are you forgetting?

352
00:25:24,533 --> 00:25:25,633
I'm a doctor!

353
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:28,000
You didn't finish med school.

354
00:25:28,067 --> 00:25:32,267
Why can't I feel
your love for me?

355
00:25:32,333 --> 00:25:33,667
I said stop it!

356
00:25:33,733 --> 00:25:36,133
How dare you question
my love for you!
